206. Reverse Linked List

to rverse a Linked List we use 3 pointers 
1) previous pointer:- at start it point to Null
2)current pointer:- at start it point to head
3)next pointer:- at start it point to head.next, (next element of head)

we iterate all over the Linked List;
while iterating 
1)we point cur.next to prev 
and 
2) then prev became cur and cur =next and next will move one step ahead;


class Solution {
    public ListNode reverseList(ListNode head) {
        if(head==null||head.next==null){
            return head;
        }
        ListNode cur=head;
        ListNode prev=null;
        ListNode Nnext =cur.next;
        while(cur!=null){
            cur.next=prev;
            prev=cur;
            cur=Nnext;
            if(Nnext!=null){
            Nnext=Nnext.next;
            }
        }
        head=prev;
        return head;
        
    }
}
